Naya: Fiddlesticks! The reports are real!
Naya: Compared to you, Pang's looking a lot more reliable!
Tica: Wait a sec. Where are these monsters coming from?
Naya: Hold on a bit longer. I'm coming!
Pang: We've got to give her a hand!
Uzziah: ...If this doesn't concern you, I suggest you leave immediately.
Naya: I'd watch your mouth. If you delay the operation of a Royal Security——
Tica: No way! Did he just summon monsters?
Naya: I command you to stop!
Uzziah: Do not approach me!
Uzziah: ...Wonderful. I've completed one...
Tica: Huh? It looks like he fainted.
Pang: ...He's injured. It's critical. He needs medical attention, otherwise...
Naya: We can't let him die like this! I've got stuff I need to ask him!
Tica: Eh!? I know! There's someone close by that can help!
Pang: Where is the kind doctor you spoke of?
Naya: This placed is booby-trapped to high heaven, how are we going to get in?
Tica: Check this out!
Aosta: You dare show your face without first finding Experiment?
Tica: Professor Clovis! We've got trouble!
Aosta: Who gave you permission to bring these grovellers to my sacred laboratory?
Tica: They're part of Team Tica, no need to worry~
Naya: Good day, I'm a Royal Security Officer of the Prai—
Aosta: I don't care. If it were the princess, I still wouldn't care.
Naya: How dare you! Who do you think you are?
Aosta: That's easy. I'm a genius. And I certainly can't rely on you, young lady.
Aosta: This is for Mr. Ceres. Bring it to him and tell him to send me a student of some caliber next time.
Aosta: And take these bumbling bumpkins with you.
Pang: This one is critically injured. We seek your help in healing him.
Aosta: (This rotten little...!?)
Tica: Professor Clovis, you can help him for sure!
Tica: Doesn't this Kingdom believe that everyone has innate value?
Naya: Forget it! We'll find another doctor!
Aosta: ......
Aosta: Bring him here.
Tica: Yea! I knew Professor Clovis was the best!
Naya: Ridiculous. If you were willing to do it in the first place, you should've just said so. Hmph!
Tica: Ooooo! So that's what he needed.
Aosta: ......
Tica: Eh? Comrade Pang, why you pulling me away?
Pang: You're bothering the doctor.
Tica: But he's the top of the food chain when it comes to Life Magic. This is the first time I've seen him heal someone. I'm really curious.
Pang: You are a student of Life Magic?
Tica: Nah, I'm in Applied Magic~
Naya: So this Professor Clovis is the master of that Experiment thingy-dingy?
Tica: Ya! I almost forgot I had to go find him!
Yamitsuki: No need. I've brought him.
Naya: Watch out, a monster!
Pang: Release the lady!
Aosta: Yamitsuki, these are my guests.
Yamitsuki: ...Understood.
Naya: That's the Experiment?
Pang: That is the being which I caught sight of earlier.
Naya: Hmm...he's not exactly a monster.
Tica: I told you!!
Experiment: Guhh......gahhh....RARGHHH!!!!
Yamitsuki: !!!!!
Naya: What's wrong? Is it normal for him to shake like this?
Aosta: (Could it be because of...?)
Tica: Comrade Naya, no worries. He's not a monster, he won't hurt anyone!
Experiment: AAAARRGHHH!!!! GURGHHHH!!!!! RORGHHH!!!
Aosta: Move away from MX46! Don't touch him!
Experiment: Guhhh...fuuhh...
Aosta: He'll be fine, we had a little hiccup, that's all.
Aosta: If, next time, you lay a finger on my experiment without my permission, you won't be walking out of this lab.
Naya: A "little" hiccup? We nearly got killed by that thing! No wonder Pang thought it was a monster...
Tica: Quick, look!
